The paper discusses the use of automated parallelism in the RoboCupSoccer 2D simulation league, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a new competition format, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses statistical analysis to validate the results, which falls under the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
